<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911121-0062</DOCNO><DOCID>911121-0062.</DOCID><HL>   Ex-Purchasing Agent   At Merrill Lynch Gets   A Prison Sentence</HL><DATE>11/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   TAXES</CO><IN>LAW AND LEGAL AFFAIRS (LAW)</IN><NS>LAW andamp; LEGAL ISSUES AND LEGISLATION (LAW)TAXES (TAX)</NS><GV>JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)</GV><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- A former purchasing agent at Merrill Lynch andamp;Co. was sentenced following a tax-evasion conviction relatedto a kickback scheme.   The former agent, John W. Hennessy, 40 years old, ofMiddletown, N.Y., was sentenced in federal District Court tofour months in prison, three years' probation and ordered tomake restitution of $7,000.</LP><TEXT>   A federal jury had found Mr. Hennessy guilty of filing afalse income tax return for the years 1984 and 1985. Anassistant U.S. attorney said evidence at the trial showedthat Mr. Hennessy took approximately $27,000 in kickbacksfrom suppliers of paper and envelopes to Merrill Lynch, whichhe failed to report as income.   Mr. Hennessy is on bail pending appeal. Merrill Lynchcooperated in the investigation.   Mr. Hennessy couldn't be reached for comment.</TEXT></DOC>